Thank you for using psyTrack!
Your feedback is very much appreciated.
If you need help with anything or experience any problems using psyTrainTrack, please send me an email and we will try to fix it or help you as soon as possible. I love hearing from you. I am constantly updating and upgrading it, so if you find any bugs please let me know.
psyTrainTrack is a product of PsycheWeb LLC, Copyright 2011, all rights reserved. psyTrainTrack was developed by Dan Boice, M.S. Dan Boice has a masters degree in Psychology and is currently completing a doctorate degree in clinical psychology with an emphasis in neuropsychology. He is interested in the integration of technology with clincial practice. He is a fellow student of psychology. He made this app primarily because he needed to use it himself.

Hi!

I discovered this great app!

Thank you to all those who supported and encouraged me as a made this app. A special thanks to Dr. Shalene Kirkley Ph.D. for her encouragement and enthusiasim for pursuing the idea back in the first year of my doctorate program. I have had a lot of fun making it and I am glad to finally be able to share it with all of you. Thank you to Tarek at Sensible Table view for a great product and support, and thanks to Dr. Touch at Cocoanetics for his help with the DTAboutViewController. Thank you to Krishna Kotecha for the starting point for the lock screen. Thank you to Apple, Inc for a making all of this amazing technology possible.
